 Bhakti poets, T. S. Eliot to J. M. Coetzee, V. S. Naipaul to the Brontës, and Kishore Kumar to Annie Ernaux, she celebrates the provincials’ humor and hilarity, playfulness and irony, belatedness and instinct for carefree accidents and freedom. Her unprecedented account of provincial life offers an alternative portrait of our modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMarginality, Social. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074979340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300277647?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300277647423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300277647/original  a978-3-11-074979-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles